gs.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045175,0.087199,0.094015,0.094221,0.098655,0.096263,0.097107,0.092304,0.084391,0.074172,0.070769,0.065728],"unified_progress":[0.056529,0.09137,0.09959,0.102,0.10034,0.10479,0.09471,0.090495,0.085353,0.071665,0.057898,0.045265]},{"section":7,"text":"It's usually associated with infections or inflammatory conditions.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042768,0.078535,0.088042,0.097659,0.095708,0.095474,0.09885,0.097429,0.090699,0.081602,0.071921,0.061313],"unified_progress":[0.043847,0.073396,0.093109,0.1008,0.10095,0.10877,0.10219,0.097227,0.089044,0.081508,0.063757,0.045407]},{"section":8,"text":"Conjunctivitis is inflammation of the eye's conjunctiva, which can be due to infections, allergies, or other inflammatory processes.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039941,0.061486,0.076397,0.086783,0.09608,0.099885,0.10605,0.10536,0.099588,0.088603,0.076918,0.062914],"unified_progress":[0.04067,0.067436,0.087226,0.096647,0.10258,0.10663,0.10372,0.099823,0.094485,0.084835,0.067273,0.048676]},{"section":9,"text":"Pleural effusion is fluid in the pleural space, which can be caused by infections, heart failure, or other systemic issues.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043839,0.058295,0.073846,0.084154,0.093868,0.098466,0.10514,0.1051,0.10056,0.090643,0.07951,0.066575],"unified_progress":[0.041083,0.064082,0.08303,0.093917,0.10016,0.10741,0.10319,0.099644,0.095589,0.086144,0.071175,0.054574]},{"section":10,"text":"The pulmonary lesions progressing to cavitation and a thin-walled cavity suggest a process that's been ongoing and possibly infectious.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038369,0.060636,0.073053,0.081399,0.088632,0.092586,0.097303,0.097771,0.096794,0.093655,0.091037,0.088764],"unified_progress":[0.037589,0.062875,0.076114,0.085275,0.091366,0.096162,0.095391,0.09673,0.096746,0.091604,0.087433,0.082716]},{"section":11,"text":"Tuberculosis comes to mind because it can cause cavities in the lungs, but the sputum findings are key here.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035596,0.056495,0.073026,0.083579,0.092381,0.096794,0.102,0.10293,0.10111,0.096386,0.08599,0.073711],"unified_progress":[0.034294,0.059776,0.077001,0.088049,0.095283,0.10042,0.1006,0.10025,0.099681,0.095777,0.082966,0.065899]},{"section":12,"text":"Mature spherules are mentioned, which makes me think of something like Coccidioides, a fungus found in the southwestern United States, including Arizona.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031232,0.059535,0.07565,0.086584,0.094227,0.098112,0.10409,0.10446,0.10017,0.094094,0.082039,0.069797],"unified_progress":[0.031934,0.060523,0.079442,0.091736,0.097734,0.10572,0.10378,0.10173,0.097942,0.092213,0.077001,0.060256]},{"section":13,"text":"Coccidioidomycosis, or valley fever, is caused by the fungus Coccidioides.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02408,0.046206,0.063451,0.077155,0.093997,0.1028,0.11703,0.12006,0.11074,0.09911,0.080692,0.064678],"unified_progress":[0.024904,0.052601,0.078183,0.094615,0.10177,0.1176,0.11222,0.1075,0.099822,0.091597,0.069509,0.049682]},{"section":14,"text":"It's endemic in arid regions like Arizona.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035507,0.056529,0.068761,0.079359,0.090915,0.097556,0.10706,0.1099,0.10529,0.097176,0.083678,0.068263],"unified_progress":[0.037351,0.062686,0.079414,0.092804,0.099223,0.10531,0.10496,0.10341,0.097828,0.092124,0.071849,0.05304]},{"section":15,"text":"The infection can cause a range of symptoms, from mild to severe.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04856,0.062438,0.072787,0.07894,0.086863,0.091095,0.097616,0.10051,0.099131,0.093402,0.088759,0.079897],"unified_progress":[0.053474,0.074776,0.082194,0.087713,0.092605,0.098293,0.096454,0.097508,0.092668,0.088604,0.076013,0.059699]},{"section":16,"text":"Pulmonary involvement is common, and it can lead to nodules, cavitation, and even dissemination.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039544,0.057774,0.069801,0.076896,0.087356,0.092799,0.10004,0.10297,0.10213,0.095681,0.091785,0.083226],"unified_progress":[0.053616,0.077901,0.084925,0.08774,0.091513,0.097351,0.094436,0.096259,0.091903,0.086871,0.075864,0.06162]},{"section":17,"text":"The skin manifestations like erythema nodosum are also known to occur with coccidioidal infection.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030722,0.050999,0.065955,0.076402,0.088794,0.09561,0.1046,0.10765,0.10556,0.099282,0.091759,0.082664],"unified_progress":[0.039168,0.064497,0.083199,0.089336,0.094885,0.10295,0.09972,0.098831,0.095336,0.089762,0.077574,0.064744]},{"section":18,"text":"Conjunctivitis might be due to the body's immune response or direct involvement of the eyes, which can happen in disseminated cases.","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035695,0.047321,0.063416,0.075804,0.088536,0.09702,0.10561,0.10955,0.11001,0.10225,0.09096,0.073833],"unified_progress":[0.033099,0.056625,0.076778,0.088056,0.096193,0.10413,0.10341,0.10357,0.101,0.097773,0.080291,0.059068]},{"section":19,"text":"Another possibility is histoplasmosis, but that's more common in the central and eastern US.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023197,0.046582,0.063636,0.075969,0.090637,0.099075,0.11116,0.11501,0.11049,0.10412,0.087956,0.072166],"unified_progress":[0.025967,0.054439,0.077323,0.092186,0.099152,0.11019,0.10868,0.10643,0.10058,0.095471,0.075277,0.054305]},{"section":20,"text":"The spherules in sputum for histoplasmosis are usually smaller and earlier in the infection.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03142,0.051691,0.067606,0.079941,0.09