on":15,"text":"That's a pretty distinctive finding.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.12299,0.099603,0.092044,0.081412,0.081757,0.081884,0.081001,0.08596,0.07493,0.050175,0.050927,0.097321],"unified_progress":[0.22221,0.086071,0.068973,0.06696,0.077145,0.07277,0.092755,0.077985,0.073275,0.058041,0.053157,0.050657]},{"section":16,"text":"Spherules are like little round structures that form when certain fungi or bacteria cause an infection.","dimension":7,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030542,0.050386,0.067454,0.084395,0.094018,0.10574,0.11287,0.11072,0.11162,0.11268,0.078604,0.040961],"unified_progress":[0.04108,0.068409,0.064537,0.10431,0.10951,0.10679,0.10555,0.10266,0.094627,0.08618,0.067288,0.049062]},{"section":17,"text":"So, putting all these pieces together - erythema nodosum, conjunctivitis, pleural effusion, cavitation, travel history to Arizona, and those spherules in the sputum - it really points towards coccidioidomycosis.","dimension":8,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020519,0.037325,0.051487,0.064909,0.077842,0.089039,0.099921,0.10527,0.11377,0.12707,0.12388,0.088975],"unified_progress":[0.031665,0.054192,0.071309,0.084181,0.092033,0.1042,0.1008,0.10108,0.10034,0.096577,0.08875,0.074871]},{"section":18,"text":"That's the fungal infection caused by Coccidioides immitis, which is known for causing these exact kinds of symptoms, especially in people who've been in the southwestern US.","dimension":7,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023693,0.034722,0.047594,0.062372,0.078283,0.094397,0.10929,0.1159,0.12526,0.13701,0.10801,0.063463],"unified_progress":[0.031253,0.052099,0.072988,0.085614,0.09412,0.10542,0.10548,0.10478,0.10003,0.095154,0.082425,0.070632]},{"section":19,"text":"Yeah, everything lines up.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.10396,0.083659,0.079026,0.072696,0.07517,0.079052,0.083463,0.093641,0.085199,0.059335,0.063303,0.